POSSIBILITY OF SUCH DAMAGE.

Note on OSI status:
    Sections 4 (attribution requirement) and 5 (no resale of the framework
    itself) make this a SOURCE-AVAILABLE license rather than strictly
    OSI-compliant "open source". All standard open-source benefits are
    preserved: free use, modification, public forks, internal deployment,
    commercial applications, commercial inference, commercial training,
    selling models trained on it, selling services built with it. The only
    restrictions are: (1) attribute in commercial products; (2) don't
    repackage the framework itself as a paid product.

Note on intent:
    PromeTorch is meant to stay free and accessible to everyone — students,
    researchers, indie developers, startups, and large companies alike.
    The author wants the framework to remain a public good while
    preventing exploitation by parties that would simply rebrand it and
    sell it. If you're unsure whether your use is permitted, the answer
    is almost certainly YES (you can use it). The very narrow "no" is
    only "don't sell PromeTorch itself as a product".
